===Etymology===
{{ME.}} < {{AF.}} < {{L.}} ''[[argumentum]]'' < ''[[arguere]]''

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[fact]] or [[statement]] used to [[support]] a [[proposition]]; a [[reason]]:
# A verbal [[dispute]]; a [[quarrel]].
# A [[process]] of [[reasoning]].
# {{context|philosophy|logic}} A [[series]] of [[statements]] [[organize]]d so that the [[final]] statement is a [[conclusion]] which is [[intend]]ed to [[follow]] [[logically]] from the [[preceding]] statements, which function as [[premise]]s.
# {{math}} The independent variable of a function.
# {{complang}} A [[value]], or reference to a value, passed to a [[function]].  <!-- call by value v.s. call by reference -->
# {{complang}} A [[parameter]] in a function definition; a [[formal argument]].
# A summary or short statement of the plot or chief points of  a book.

====Usage notes====
*({{complang}} formal argument) The use of the word '''argument''' without '''formal''' as a qualifier is common, but is a loose usage. [[parameter|Parameter]] is more correct.

